                    <span>It was astounded by what descriped in the opening of the book: at first, the events seem to be at the current, but then they were happened at the last turn of century!<p>It is still the best anlaysis of network economy among 5 books that I read about, though 2 of which are also from Harvard.  This book just touches the heart of network economy, and it gives me a lot to further analyze the continuous economics events happening in the globe.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Fascinating</div>
